<HEADLINE> Clinton Should Be Judged Politically: Museveni </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni said Wednesday afternoon that U.S. President Bill
Clinton should be judged politically, not according to his
private life.
</P>
<P>
Museveni made the comment at the press conference at State
House here when asked about Clinton's alleged affair with former
White House intern Monica Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
"Our assessment of Clinton is political, not private,"
Museveni told reporters, adding, "when he bombed Sudan, we are
very happy."
</P>
<P>
Europe and America have different cultures with Africans, so
it is quite difficult to judge by our cultural and ethical
standards, he noted.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, he also answered questions on
Uganda's attitude to the nine-week-long Congo (K) conflict,
security in the country and local economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
