<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: Security Council Should Stick to Principles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the Untied Nations should strictly adhere to the purposes and
principles of the Charter of the United Nations in dealing with
internal conflicts of countries, China stressed here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 53rd session of the General Assembly on the work
of the Security Council, Chinese Deputy Permanent Representative
to the United Nations, Shen Guofang, said in dealing with these
important and complicated issues, the Security Council should act
upon the consent or request of countries involved and exert its
utmost effort to help resolve the conflict through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Shen said China was not in favor of interference in the
internal affairs of a country in the name of alleviating
humanitarian crisis, or the use of military threat or intervention
with willful invocation of the Charter of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador said China was also opposed to putting all the
problems in the conflict areas on the agenda of the Council, which
did not conform to the principles guiding the division of work
among the various organs of the United Nations, nor did it
facilitate the effective functioning of other organs of U.N.,
especially the General Assembly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
