<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police to Interrogate Tanzania Bombing Suspect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Dar es Salaam-based
Kisutu Resident Magistrate's Court allowed Wednesday a suspect
involved in the bombing of U.S. embassy to be handed back to
police custody for further interrogation.
</P>
<P>
Delivering the ruling, Principal Resident Magistrate Projestus
Lugazia told the court that the issue of interrogating the
suspect, Mustafa Mahmoud Said Ahmed, an Egyptian, is to make sure
the prosecution is correct.
</P>
<P>
However, Defense Counsel Abdul Mwengera objected the ruling
said he will file an application of appeal to the High Court.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Leonard Mashaka, the prosecutor and assistant
commissioner of police (ACP), requested the court to have Ahmed
who is at Segerea Remand Prison, sent back to the Central Police
Station for seven days of further interrogation.
</P>
<P>
But his request was objected by Mwengera who said no law can
be found to give power to the court to transfer the accused
person from remand prison back to police custody for
interrogation.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people were killed and more than 70 others were
injured in the bomb blast of U.S. embassy in Dar es Salaam on
August 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
