<HEADLINE> Downpour Leaves 500 Zanzibar Residents Homeless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Three days of continuous
downpour have washed away more than 200 houses in the Zanzibar
isles, leaving some 500 people homeless and raising fears of
cholera outbreak.
</P>
<P>
Areas affected in the Indian isles include Jang'ombe, Uwanja,
Farasi, Sebuleni, Kwahani and Mpendaye, media reports said
Thursday, adding that people were seen escaping with belongings
on their heads and fleeing their houses built in valleys.
</P>
<P>
Government health officials have appealed to people to drink
boiled water to avoid water-borne diseases like cholera. The
isles were frequently attacked by cholera for lack of toilets and
garbage disposal facilities. 
</P>
