<HEADLINE> Chinese Rural Industry Confident About Reaching Year's Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China's rural industries
believe that they can reach this year's economic growth target of
18 percent, according to China Information News.
</P>
<P>
In the first eight months, Chinese township and village
enterprises had 1.4 trillion yuan in added value output, up 15.6
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the next few months, it said, rural industry will fare even
better as the central government plans to inject more funds into
water resources and other infrastructure projects to increase
domestic demand and speed up economic development.
</P>
<P>
The disaster relief measures and reconstruction after the
severe floods in southern and northeastern parts of China in the
summer also mean an increased demand for rural industry, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Rural industry produces 95 percent of the country's bricks and
tile, 40 percent of its cement, and has a sizable share of the
construction, machinery and garment industries.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural ministry, which supervises rural industry,
told the newspaper that rural industry is certain to develop well
in the coming months and reach the annual growth target. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
