<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CICB Reports Sharp Rise in Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The China Industrial and
Commercial Bank (CICB) today reported substantial increase in
loans during the first three quarters of the year to support
national economic growth.
</P>
<P>
CICB's outstanding loan volume reached 2.09 trillion yuan by
the end of September, up 183.3 billion yuan from at the beginning
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that CICB's loan volume has increased sharply
since the first quarter of the year, with a jump of 74.3 billion
yuan for the second quarter and a rise of 101.4 billion yuan for
the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that the greatest share of loans has been
channeled to 1,000 major enterprises and key state construction
projects. Outstanding loans to enterprises hit 354.7 billion yuan
by the end of August, up 30.6 billion yuan from at the beginning
of the year and representing 21.4 percent of the total increase.
</P>
<P>
Rapid growth has also been recorded in loans for
infrastructure, basic industries and housing construction. CICB
granted loans totalling 51.9 billion yuan to projects in related
areas during the first nine months, up 17.4 billion yuan on last
year's corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
Loans to small and medium-sized enterprises grew by over 30
billion yuan in the nine months to September, with outstanding
loans to businesses with different forms of ownership hitting
987.2 billion yuan, up 66.4 billion yuan from at the beginning of
the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981022.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Puts Forward New Tasks for Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen Thursday put forward seven measures for the
current government to free itself from being the hostage of
minority politicians and continue to fulfill its work in a good
manner.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen proposed the measures in a lengthy important speech he
made at Chaktomuk Hall to celebrate King Norodom Sihanouk's 76th
birthday, the Independence Day and the 7th anniversary of the
signing of the Paris Peace Accord on Cambodia, which was signed on
October 23, 1991 by 19 countries.
</P>
<P>
"Up to now, although we are still optimistic that the new
government will likely come into being in the near future, in a
sense of (the) responsibility of the current government, I think
that we have wasted a lot of valuable time," Hun Sen said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, he has the historic duty to run the country
till a new government is set up, and it is also for the sake of
the nation and the suffering and hardship of the people.
</P>
<P>
The measures put forward by him include:
</P>
<P>
-- To continue implementing in strict manner the eight-point
security measures defined by him earlier last year;
</P>
<P>
-- The current government fulfills its tasks in a good manner,
and not abandon any tasks while waiting for the new government to
be formed;
</P>
<P>
-- To put forward immediately new measures for combating
corruption and other negative activities which create difficulty
to investors and businessmen, such as kidnapping, drug trafficking
and armed robbery;
</P>
<P>
-- New policy regarding the water issue be implemented in an
urgent manner without delay. The management of forest, which was
the weakest point of the Royal Government, be strengthened in a
strong manner;
</P>
<P>
-- Strong encouragement be made toward the investors and all
businessmen in the country;
</P>
<P>
-- To strengthen the management of budget and fiscal affairs;
</P>
<P>
-- To speed up the reform in the judicial system.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Hun Sen reviewed the achievements made by the
Royal Government in the past seven years but also pointed out the
problems the Cambodian people are still facing now in economy,
social stability, and livelihood.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen condemned the opposition for using violent illegal
demonstrations in implementing a dangerous plan, such as inciting
uprisings in part of the armed forces, expanding the anarchy to
various places and attempting to kill leaders of the government.
</P>
<P>
On the summit among the country's three major parties, Hun Sen
said that the outstanding problem is that the elected political
parties and the elected parliamentarians have to do the work for
the sake of the people who voted for them.
</P>
<P>
"Considering the results of the summit meeting on September 22,
1998 in Siem Reap under the chairmanship of the King, if these are
strictly respected, there seems no need to hold another summit,"
he said. However, he warned that if going against the spirit of
these results, even though the meeting is held several times, in
any venue, "no results will be achieved."
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen expressed his hope that the political parties and the
elected parliamentarians will not create new obstacles but
actively take part in solving the problem for the sake of the
nation and people.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia held the National Assembly election on July 26, this
year. The ruling Cambodia People's Party (CPP) won the most seats,
followed by the FUNCINPEC Party and the Sam Rainsy Party, but the
CPP did not secure enough seats to govern alone under the
Constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
