<HEADLINE> Jailed Daily Staff Released on Bail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Publisher of the banned
moderate daily Tous, Mohammad Javad Hessari, and another staff
member Ebrahim Nabavi were released on bail, the official news
agency IRNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Judicial sources told IRNA that Hessari and Nabavi were
released on Wednesday, but they did not say why.
</P>
<P>
Four members of the daily's editorial board were arrested last
month on charges of publishing materials against national
security and the state, after Tous was ordered to close down on
September 16.
</P>
<P>
Tous, named after an ancient Iranian city, was accused of
publishing material of defamatory character against the late
spiritual leader Ayatollah Musavi Khomenei.
</P>
<P>
Tous, which strongly supported moderate President Mohammad
Khatami, vowed to fight for the freedom of expression in the
country. This angered the powerful conservatives who dominate the
judiciary.
</P>
<P>
One of the four arrested, Hamid Reza Jalaeipour, was released
on bail last week in the wake of the petition by his mother to the
supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
There was no information about the fourth in custody.  
</P>
</TEXT>
