<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Customs Confiscates Illegal Video Disks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Customs Office
said today it seized more than 1.2 million smuggled video discs
during a recent crackdown on pornographic and pirated publications.
</P>
<P>
On September 22, officers of the Panyu branch of Guangzhou
Customs, boarded a cargo vessel near the Pearl River estuary and
discovered 777 cases of pirated VCDs and CVDs, with the illegal
cache of 757,000 items including 30,000 pornographic publications.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers intercepted a boat in the same area on the
night of October 17 and confiscated 460,000 video discs, 152
Motorola walkie-talkies and four CD players.
</P>
<P>
The seizures were part of an extensive local campaign against
pornographic and pirated publications since the beginning of this
year, with related efforts leading to the seizure of 4.5 million
smuggled video discs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
