<HEADLINE> Legal Service Center in Shanghai Caters to Needs of Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Elderly Legal
Service Center has provided consultation, mediation and other
services for more than 700 elderly people since it was established
about a month ago.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has more than 2.3 million people above the age of 60,
or 17.8 percent of the population.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up by the Municipal Civil Affairs Bureau and
the Municipal Committee for the Aged to help them in solving
problems, many of which are disputes among family members.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 30 college students working in the center
as volunteers.
</P>
<P>
"What we learn here can't be learned in the classroom," said
Jiang Hankang, a student at the Law Institute of Shanghai
University, who adds that he feels that offering to help the
elderly with his legal knowledge is significant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
