<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Hainan Province Building Gas Pipe Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The second stage of a gas
pipeline running around the island province of Hainan in south
China will begin construction this year, Vice-Governor Yu Xun said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The 177.6-km pipeline project and a third stage will cost 2.66
billion yuan (321 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The ring is 904.3 kilometers in all. The first stage, a 116-km
line from Sanya to Dongfang, was completed in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to help ease the short fuel supply and
promote industrial development in the province, which is the
largest special economic zone of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
