<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed unchanged here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was stable at 1,842 points with a turnover of
71.5 million N.Z. dollars (37.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, AMP, Fletcher Building, Fletcher
Paper and Fletcher Energy closed unchanged at 2,220, 229, 107 and
360 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Telecom was the biggest loser, down 12 cents to 783 cents,
while Air New Zealand the biggest winner, up 10 cents to 172
cents.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey lost 6 cents to 153 cents. Fletcher forest
put on 4 cents to 60 cents. Auckland Airport and Brierley
Investments were up 2 cents each to 192 and 46 cents respectively.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
