<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Capital Exchange Marks One Year Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Capital Exchange -
Sofia Inc marked its first anniversary Wednesday with shares of
993 companies traded on the market.
</P>
<P>
A total of 15,482 deals were closed in the year, involving the
sale of 30,875,343 shares worth nearly 260,000 million leva (about
14 million U.S. dollars), the company's executive director Georgi
Prohaski told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He also said market capitalization of the partnerships on sale
was some 2,000 million Deutsche marks (about 1,250 million
dollars), of which some 60-70 are offered on the exchange.
</P>
<P>
"We created normal working conditions for the brokers and
became a real institution for trade in securities," Prohaski said.
</P>
<P>
Six deals were closed a year ago at the first session of
Bulgarian Capital Exchange - Sofia Inc, which was opened by Prime
Minister Ivan Kostov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
