<HEADLINE> Infrastructure Conference Opens in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Infranet '98, a three-day
conference-cum-exposition on infrastructure, opened here Thursday
with focus on surface transport, urban infrastructure and
industrial estates and townships.
</P>
<P>
The aspects covered in surface transport include roads,
bridges, highways, ports and airports. Housing, water management
systems, drainage and water supply will be covered under urban
infrastructure, official sources here said.
</P>
<P>
Infranet '98 will also focus on specific projects aiming at
providing a forum for direct interaction among relevant agencies,
government and private developers for finalizing a concrete action
plan for India's infrastructure development.
</P>
<P>
Around 23 business suits are being set up at the conference
venue, which will work as private offices for senior
representatives of project sponsors. Singapore and Malaysia will
also share their experience in the development of urban
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The conference was organized by the Confederation of Indian
Industry. Infrastructure construction still remains the main
bottleneck for rapid industry development in India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
