<HEADLINE> Heroin Hauled at Sri Lanka's Int'l Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Police Narcotics
Bureau made a massive haul of heroin at the Colombo International
Airport on Tuesday night, according to police sources Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said they were able to recover 3.8 kilos of heroin
with a current street value of over 6.5 million RS (97,000 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
An Indian national who had attempted to smuggle the heroin
concealed inside four plastic mats was arrested.
</P>
<P>
Investigations had revealed that the man was a regular visitor
to Sri Lanka and it was his fifth time this year. 
</P>
