<DOCNO> XIE19981022.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian Parliament Approves Draft Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian parliament, the
People's Assembly, on Wednesday approved a draft new constitution
on which the Albanians will vote in a referendum next month.
</P>
<P>
The draft, which had been deliberated in the parliament,
controlled by the ruling coalition, for nearly two weeks, was
carried with 115 votes for and one abstention. The opposition
Democratic Party boycott the deliberation and the voting.
</P>
<P>
Under a decree issued by Albanian President Rexhep Meidani
Wednesday night, a referendum will be held on November 22 to
decide the fate of the new basic law.
</P>
<P>
The old constitution was abolished in the early 1990s after the
fall of the government led by the Albanian Party of Labor. And
Albania has been running without a constitution since.
</P>
<P>
A previous draft constitution, worked out by the government led
by former president Sali Berisha of the Democratic Party, was
rejected by a referendum in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
