<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province Reports Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north
China expects to get 28.88 million tons of grain this year,
982,000 tons more than the record high in 1996, an official of the
provincial statistics bureau said today.
</P>
<P>
The bountiful harvest comes in spite of a smaller summer
harvest as a result of a drought in the southern part of the
province and floods in the northern part.
</P>
<P>
The bureau estimated the province's autumn harvest at 16.22
million tons, an increase of 2.17 million tons over last year.
</P>
<P>
The increased grain output was made possible by expanded
growing areas and the wider and more effective application of
agricultural machinery and technology, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
