<HEADLINE> NBA Player Anderson Pleads Guilty in Drug Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- NBA star Greg Anderson has
pleaded guilty to a federal drug trafficking charge Tuesday in
Mississippi, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Anderson, a free agent center who charged with one count of
possession of cocaine with intent to distribute, made his plea
Tuesday in U.S. District Court in Biloxi. He faces a maximum four
years in prison and a 2 million U.S. dollars fine.
</P>
<P>
Two other counts of possession and a count of trafficking and
forfeiture were dropped.
</P>
<P>
On June 25, federal authorities accused Anderson and three
other men of making deals for cocaine and carrying the drugs from
Houston to Biloxi.
</P>
<P>
Anderson was detained but not arrested on May 20 at a hotel
during an FBI sting operation.
</P>
<P>
Anderson played for the Atlanta Hawks last season with a
10-year NBA history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
