<HEADLINE> Laudrup Warns Before Copenhagen Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Brian Laudrup has warned his
Chelsea team-mates not to fall foul of complacency as they bid to
continue their defence of the Cup Winners' Cup against FC
Copenhagen at Stamford Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The Blues struggled to beat another Scandinavian side
Helsingborgs in the first round, an unconvincing 1-0 home win
followed by a 0-0 draw in Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Danish star Laudrup is well aware that Gianluca Vialli's side
will need to improve to beat a Copenhagen side he rates far
higher than the Swedish part-timers.
</P>
<P>
"I have played with some of the players and I've said to the
boys here that in my opinion they are certainly a stronger side
than Helsingborgs so we know it's not going to be an easy game to
play in," Laudrup said.
</P>
<P>
"They will make it difficult for us. For them it's a
tremendous draw to play Chelsea and if they get something out of
the game on Thursday it will be a tremendous result for FC
Copenhagen and Danish football in general.
</P>
<P>
"They're a typical Scandinavian side. They're very strong,
they can run all day and put a lot of pressure on their opponents.
</P>
<P>
"They will hope we will look at them and think it's going to
be an easy game and Chelsea are favorites for the game.
</P>
<P>
"But they have some good experienced and talented players and
we'll have to be aware they can do a lot of damage. I think
Bjarne Goldbaek and Peter Nielsen are the two main threats, " he
said. 
</P>
