<HEADLINE> Kazakh President to Run in Coming Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev Tuesday announced he would run in the presidential
election to be held on January 10, 1999, the kazakhstan Telegraph
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said in a statement that he would do his best to
safeguard national independence, stability and concord, and let
the people feel happier and more secure.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the face of grave testing of the international
financial crisis, especially that of Russia's political and
financial crises, he is taking emergency measures to alleviate the
negative effects on the people's livelihood.
</P>
<P>
When the parliament decided on October 8 to hold the
presidential election ahead of time, Nazarbayev said he had not
decided whether to run or not.
</P>
<P>
He made the campaigning decision after being urged by his own
Party of National Unity, the Democratic Party and some other
political parties and social groups.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say Nazarbayev and former prime minister Akezhan
Kazhegeldin will be the two main rivals in the campaign.
Serikbolsyn Abdildin, first secretary of the Kazakhstan Communist
Party, will also contest. 
</P>
