<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Madrid, Manchester United Score Big Wins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- European champions Real Madrid
and Manchester United gained big wins in their European
Champion's League campaign on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid trounced Austrians Sturm Graz 6-1 while Manchester
United demolished Brondby 6-2 in Copenhagen, a new away goals
record in the six-year history of the Champions' League.
</P>
<P>
Those results evoked memories of European glory days gone-by
for both Real and United -- while Brazilian striker Ronaldo
reminded everyone that he is still a force to be reckoned with
after his recent injury woes.
</P>
<P>
He scored Inter Milan's second in their 2-1 defeat of Spartak
Moscow which ended the last 100 per cent record in the
competition and left Real Madrid, Spartak and Inter all level
with six points in Group C.
</P>
<P>
Serhiy Rebrov of Dynamo Kiev stunned more than 70,000 Arsenal
fans at Wembley Stadium with a last-minute equalizer for a share
of the points in a 1-1 draw in Group E, while Juventus's bid to
reach the final for the fourth successive season became further
derailed when they drew 0-0 at Athletic Bilbao -- their third
successive draw in Group B.
</P>
<P>
That section is topped by Norwegians Rosenborg Trondheim who
beat Galatasaray 3-0 thanks to a memorable second-half hat-trick
from Sigurd Rushfeldt.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich won the clash of the giants against Barcelona
with Steffen Effenberg scoring the only goal of their Group D
match on the stroke of halftime.
</P>
<P>
There was also an impressive win for HJK Helsinki of Finland,
who pulled off the shock result of the night beating former
European champions Benfica of Portugal 2-0 at home with first
half goals from Mika Lehkosua and Mikka Kottila.
</P>
<P>
Helsinki, widely believed to be nothing more than the whipping
boys in Group F, moved to second in the table on four points,
three behind Kaiserslautern of Germany, who won 2-1 at PSV
Eindhoven. Benfica prop up the group with the Dutch side, both on
three points.
</P>
<P>
Porto had an impressive win in Group A defeating Croatia
Zagreb 3-0 with Zlatko Zahovic scoring twice and Doriva Junior
once in Group A, but that section is surprisingly topped by
Olympiakos Piraeus who beat Ajax Amsterdam 1-0 at home. They have
seven points from three matches, three more than Ajax and Porto.
</P>
</TEXT>
