<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rice Output Expected to Drop This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bureau of
Statistics has estimated that Indonesia's unhulled dry rice output
in 1998 will total 46.44 million tons, down by 5.94 percent from
the preceding year.
</P>
<P>
The drop would be attributable to a decline in rice fields'
productivity by 2.31 quintals per hectare nationwide, the agency
said in a press release published by Antara News Agency Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The total area of paddy fields is expected to shrink by 85,000
hectares or 0.76 percent this year, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's unhulled dry rice output last year stood at 49.39
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Rice productivity is affected by the fact that farmers only
used urea fertilizer during the planting season, the agency said,
adding that most farmers did not use triple superphosphate
fertilizer because of their higher prices.
</P>
<P>
Pest attacks on rice plants could not be optimally dealt with
as many farmers could not afford highly-priced pesticides, the
agency added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
