<HEADLINE> China's Largest Nuclear Power Plant Proceeds Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Lianyungang
Nuclear Power Plant in east China's Jiangsu Province went into the
stage of enclosed operations on Tuesday, local sources said today.
</P>
<P>
In this stage, all staff, visitors and vehicles going in and
out of the work site must show valid certificates.
</P>
<P>
The project officially began on February 27 and is the largest
high-tech cooperation project between China and Russia, with a
designed power generating capacity of six million kw. Construction
work will be divided into three phases, with two one-million-kw
pressurized water reactors installed in each of the three phases.
</P>
<P>
In the first phase of construction, two reactors will begin
operations in 2004 and 2005 respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
