<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-French Fire-Fighter Training Center Set up in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-French educational
center to train senior Chinese fire-fighting police officials has
been set up in Tianjin, the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Beichen District, a one-hour drive from Beijing,
the center has completed its first construction phase, a building
area of 10,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
France has provided part of the training equipment for the
center in accordance with an agreement signed by the two countries
last year.
</P>
<P>
The students at the center will receive field training geared
to China's features, and also study the fire-fighting techniques
of developed countries.
</P>
<P>
China has suffered from severe fire disasters in recent years,
threatening lives, property and social security.  
</P>
</TEXT>
