<HEADLINE> Indonesian President to Attend APEC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie said he will attend the summit of the Asia Pacific
Economic Cooperation Forum (APEC) scheduled for November 17 in
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
"God willing, I will attend," the president said in an
interview with Indonesian television stations TVRI and RCTI on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Habibie said the meeting was crucial because APEC leaders would
be able to exchange views on increased economic cooperation in
Asia and the Pacific.
</P>
<P>
However, he said the Indonesian delegation to the Kuala Lumpur
meeting would likely be different from those to the previous APEC
meetings.
</P>
<P>
The problem was that the Indonesia had no vice president, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In the past, if the president traveled to other cities or
countries, the vice president remained in Jakarta and the other
way around.
</P>
<P>
"Now the problem is that we have no vice president. Therefore,
I will leave (for Malaysia) after I perform the Subuh (early
morning) prayers and return home before the Magrib (early evening)
prayers," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
