<DOCNO> XIE19981022.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Merapi Volcano Active Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Mount Merapi, Indonesia's most
active volcano in Central Java, has resumed spewing hot gasses
this week, Antara News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The hot gasses in the direction of River Lamat's lower reaches
covered a distance of up to 1.3 kilometers, which prompted the
authorities to call on villagers in the area to stay alert.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the results of visual as well as instrumental
observations, Mount Merapi was still considered a threat to its
surroundings, head of the volcanic technology research and
development institute Mas Atje Purbawita said.
</P>
<P>
Mount Merapi, 2,968-meter high and one the most active
volcanoes in Indonesia, last erupted on July 11, spilling out hot
fumes and ashes.
</P>
<P>
Three major eruptions have been recorded in the past, one of
which occurred in 1930 when 1,300 people were killed. The other
two eruptions were in 1994 and 1997, when a total of 88 people
died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
