<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks closed higher on
Wednesday with technology stocks posting more gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 13.38 to 8519.23 in the
sixth consecutive gaining session, while the technology-laced
Nasdaq composite index rose a staggering 35.56 to 1674.75 as a
result of strong earnings reported by large computer companies.
</P>
<P>
Nasdaq component Microsoft chalked a 154 percent growth in the
third quarter's earnings to 1.68 billion U.S. dollars. Both
Microsoft and the Dow component IBM saw big gains in their stocks
for their better record of earnings.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip barometer has so far gained 580 points since last
Wednesday with most of the winning points coming from the interest
cut by the Federal Reserve last Thursday, but the index is still
819 points below its peak of 9337.97 on July 17.
</P>
<P>
Advances led declines by a slim margin on Wednesday, with
trading volume totaling 740 million shares, down from 947 million
a session earlier on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 5.99 to 1069.92, the NYSE
composite index rose 1.12 to 529.40, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 4.28 to 620.55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
