<DOCNO> XIE19981022.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Software Maker CA to Expand Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International (CA), a leading provider of business software in the
U.S., announced a 400,000 square foot expansion of its corporate
headquarters in New York on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An additional 1,000 employees will be accommodated over the next
year as a result of the expansion and over 8,000 are expected to
be working in the Long Island headquarters instead of the 2,300
now, said CA Chairman and CEO Charles Wang.
</P>
<P>
The project features new office and research and development
facilities and a technical training center.
</P>
<P>
The program was seen as an expression of self-confidence at a
time when a number of U.S. companies are cutting their jobs due to
the impact of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
CA's revenue rose 17 percent to 4.7 billion U.S. dollars in the
financial year 1998, according to its annual report.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1976 and headquartered on Long Island in 1979, CA's
business has grown to 160 offices in 43 countries with its
workforce increasing to 11,000 worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The company develops, licenses and supports more than 500
integrated products that include enterprise computing and
information management, application development, manufacturing and
financial applications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
