<HEADLINE> China: UN Should Attach Greater Importance to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The importance that the
United Nations Security Council was requested to attach to African
issues must be translated into concrete deeds, China stressed here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 53rd session of the General Assembly on the work
of the Security Council, Chinese Deputy Permanent Representative
to the United Nations, Shen Guofang, said the prolonged turmoil on
the African continent had evolved against profound historical
background and was the result of various complex internal and
external factors.
</P>
<P>
Shen said China had always been in the position that the
Council should consider seriously the legitimate demand of African
countries, respond positively to their appeal and give effective
support and coordination to the efforts of African countries and
regional organizations in solving the problems in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the Security Council had held meetings at the level
of foreign ministers for two consecutive years to discuss,
exclusively, the problems in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador expressed the hope that the Council's
discussions on the African issue would go deeper on substantive
issues, so as to find an effective way to help accommodate the
real concern of African countries and promote lasting stability
and development in Africa.  
