<HEADLINE> China Hosts Symposium on International Bulk Cargo Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on
bulk cargo transport opened today in the city of Tianjin, the
largest port in northern China.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 shipowners, brokers, and port navigation experts
from over 30 countries and regions, including the United States,
Britain, France, Australia and Japan are attending the
two-day symposium.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is jointly sponsored by COSCO (China Ocean
Shipping Corporation) Bulk Carrier Ltd. and the China Shipowners
Association's Bulk Cargo Transport Committee.
</P>
<P>
China imports and exports 200 million tons of goods annually,
and Asian ocean shipping accounts for more than a half of the
world's total bulk cargo.
</P>
<P>
COSCO is one of the world's major bulk carriers, with 106 large
vessels of 5.7 million dwt, and service to more than 1,000 cities
all over the world.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, held when the international shipping market is
dull, provides a forum for discussing the latest developments in
international bulk cargo, trends in the next century, and new
strategies to standardize international bulk transport business
for mutual benefit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
