<HEADLINE> Chinese Building Materials Industry Revises Growth Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China has revised upward the
growth target of its building materials industry this year from
six to seven percent to seven to eight percent, today's Market
Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The upward revision by the State Building Materials Industry
Bureau followed the central government's decision to increase the
amount of spending on infrastructure, and the demand created by
post-flood reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
A bureau study of 70 major cement producers showed combined
sales of 5.44 million tons in September, up 19.2 percent from the
same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Plate glass is becoming more expensive, with a study of 23
factories showing prices higher in September than in August, which
was already higher than for the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Plate glass prices had been falling until June, when the bureau
set a bottom price to protect the manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The bureau estimates that China will produce 520 million tons
of cement this year, up 1.6 percent from last year, and 170
million weight cases of plate glass, up 2.4 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
