<HEADLINE> Mozambique Bans Youths From Night Clubs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican parliament
passed a law Wednesday, banning youths under 18 years of age from
some night clubs.
</P>
<P>
Tarciso Jemusse, parliament member of the Democratic Union
Party said at the parliament meeting that the new law is an
attempt to rebuild moral principles and protect children from
unhealthy activities.
</P>
<P>
He said that the degradation of the morality in some
Mozambicans has to some extend a lot to do with the malpractice
of some night clubs and disco halls.
</P>
<P>
Angelina Enoque, a parliament member from the opposition
National Resistance Movement (Renamo), said that that the law
would be very helpful in cracking down on some illegal
activities, since some night clubs have been found to conniving
youths for sex activities.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who breaks the law would face a fine of 4,000 to 50,000
U.S. Dollars, or six months to 12 years of imprisonment,
according to the law.  
</P>
