<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's parliamentary
committee on social service Wednesday pleaded with the Uganda
Medical Workers Union (UMWU) to call off their impending strike
and ask the government to solve the problems through peaceful
means.
</P>
<P>
The committee made this appeal in response to the UMWU's
planned strike on November 29, demanding better working
conditions and payment, the New Vision paper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The UMWU members should think twice on the deadline and
withhold the strike until all channels have been tried, Jane
Akwero, a woman MP from northern district of Gulu was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
