to striking because of absence of a mechanism through which they
can air their grievances.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, President Yoweri Museveni said that the
medical workers are underpaid and promised to solve the problem
soon.
</P>
<P>
But he fiercely opposed strikes by the medical staff, because
he said if the doctors who control people's lives go on strike,
some patients may die.
</P>
<P>
He said he would sack the doctors who go to the street instead
of expressing their complaints through peaceful means. 
</P>
