<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia to Strengthen Management of Forest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen vowed Thursday to take strong measures to control
the illegal logging and timber exports in order to keep the
sustainability of the forest and protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen made an important speech on a rally to mark King
Norodom Sihanouk's 76th birthday, the Independence Day (November
9) and the 7th anniversary of the signing of Paris Peace Accords
on Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen admitted in his speech," the forest issue is the
weakest point of the Royal Government of the first term. The
anarchy in logging happened seriously during the period of 1994 to
1998. We can say that in the past four years the forest have been
most seriously destroyed in the thousand-year history of
Cambodia."
</P>
<P>
Environmental groups warned logging in Cambodia is out of
control and Cambodia's forest will be logged out within three to
five years unless the industry can be properly regulated.
</P>
<P>
To keep the sustainability of the forest, which is the rare
natural resource, and protect the environment, the Royal
Government declared four point measures:
</P>
<P>
-- To put an end to permission for the investment in wood
processing;
</P>
<P>
-- To begin to review all contracts on forest concession, and
cancel the contracts having yet to be implemented. The forest
zones belonging to the canceled contracts should not be granted to
any other company, but be set in the reserve zones or wildlife
refuge or national parks under the strict management of the
Ministry of Agriculture, Ministry of Environment and the local
authorities;
</P>
<P>
-- As for the forest concession which implemented in accordance
with the contracts must equip with more modern processing means in
order to increase the wood value as well as the employment for the
people;
</P>
<P>
-- To conduct a review on the draft law on the forest
management and prepare decree on the forest management. Those who
are involved in illegal logging or illegal export must be
identified and punished immediately. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
