<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Lawyers to Act as Contract Notaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Justice
granted approval today for 121 Hong Kong lawyers to act as
contract notaries public, bringing the total number to nearly 200.
</P>
<P>
The new group represents the largest number of approvals since
China resumed sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Justice Gao Changli noted that contracted notaries
public have dealt with large volume of notary documents involving
inland China over the past 10 years. He said their efforts have
helped to safeguard the legitimate rights of Hong Kong residents
and legal entities, and have promoted civil affairs and economic
and legal exchanges between the region and inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Gao said the notaries public are playing an increasingly
important role in safeguarding Hong Kong's legal system and
promoting prosperity and stability in the region, as well as
exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Justice has authorized Hong Kong lawyers to
deal with notarization of economic and civil affairs for hong Kong
residents and corporate legal entities engaged in inland
activities since 1981.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted notaries have issued over 500,000 notary documents
over the past 10-odd years alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
