<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Deadlock of Mideast Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The only option for resolving
the disputes between Arabian nations and Israel is peace
talks, said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang at
today's routine press conference.
</P>
<P>
He said the current peace talks between the leaders of Arabian
countries and Israel have entered "a crucial moment."
</P>
<P>
The deadlock of the peace process would harmful to the Arabian
and Israeli sides, but also to security in the Middle East, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the peace talks should continue on the basis of
relevant United Nations' resolutions and in line with the
principle of "land for peace" as agreed by all relevant parties in
the Madrid Conference.
</P>
<P>
China hopes the international community to make greater efforts
for the advance of the peace talks to realize a thorough, fair and
lasting peace in the Middle East, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
