<HEADLINE> U.S. Air Force Jet Crashes in Nevada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, October 22 (Xinhua) -- U.S. military officials
confirmed early Thursday morning that an F-15E fighter jet with
two pilots aboard crashed Wednesday night during a training
mission inside the state of Nevada.
</P>
<P>
Staff Sgt. Sonja Whittington at the Mountain Home Air Force
Base in neighboring state of Idaho said the fate of the two people
was not known and the cause of crash was under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The jet crashed shortly after 9 p.m. near McDermitt, a town
near the border between Nevada and Idaho, said Whittington, adding
that the search and rescue crews were on their way to the remote
site late Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
