<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Acknowledges Democracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie Thursday acknowledged that the democratic system is quite
complicated as it thrives only among people who think maturely.
</P>
<P>
"Democracy can only thrive if the people have the
broad-mindedness and the tolerance to accept different opinions in
a condition where heterogeneity is respected," the president said.
</P>
<P>
Opening the 5th national congress of the ruling Golkar
(Functional Group)-affiliated organization AMPI at the State
Palace here, Habibie said democracy could develop only if all
parties are ready to uphold political ethics, justice and legal
norms.
</P>
<P>
"Otherwise, democracy will only turn into a joke that will make
the people laugh. Moreover, democracy can turn into anarchy if the
political activists are immature in terms of attitude," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the reform process, the president stressed that the process
should be conducted democratically.
</P>
<P>
"It is impossible to achieve democracy through anarchic ways,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He reminded the people that democracy is not identical with the
freedom to curse or slander one another. On the contrary,
democracy should respect differences even if one group disagrees
with another group's ideas, he said.
</P>
<P>
In democracy, every party has the right to exist and to be
respected, the president said, adding that the only party that
does not deserve this right is one whose ideology is against
democracy itself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
