Nabavi were released on bail Wednesday while another member Hamid
Reza Jalaeipour was set free on bail last week following a
petition by his mother to the supreme leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
The four men were arrested last month on charges of launching
activities against national security and interests.
</P>
<P>
Tous, which was named after an ancient Iranian city, was
ordered to close on September 16 for publishing material with
defamatory character against the late Iranian supreme leader
Ayatollah Musavi Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
The daily has all along had troubles with the powerful
conservative-dominated judiciary as it, believed by many,
strongly supports the moderate President Mohammad Khatami and has
vowed to fight for freedom of expression in the country. 
</P>
