<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Congress of Trade
Unions (ZCTU) has urged teachers to call off their month-long
strike as they have made their point known.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail Thursday quoted ZCTU General-Secretary Alec
Chirwa as saying that the teachers should now leave the matter in
the hands of the Zambia National Union of Teachers (ZNUT).
</P>
