public services workers is not new but ZCTU is disappointed with
the government for taking too long to address the plight of the
workers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chirwa also called on public service unions to take advantage
of the lapsing of the wage freeze and open negotiations with the
government so that they can be concluded in good time.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, striking teachers in Livingstone,
southern Zambia, have vowed never to return to class despite the
appeal made earlier this week by Education Minister Godfrey
Miyanda.
</P>
<P>
ZNUT's provincial organizing secretary Keith Mabuku said that
all the teachers from 26 primarychools in the district of
Livingstone are on strike and will only meet Friday to review the
minister's appeal.
</P>
<P>
Over 30,000 pupils in the district are affected because of the
strike.
</P>
<P>
Teachers in Livingstone and many other parts of the country
have been on strike for one month demanding better conditions of
service and wages. 
