<HEADLINE> 25 People Charred to Death in Southern India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 people were
charred to death and over a dozen others suffered severe burns
when a bus turned turtle and caught fire near Tottayam district,
about 1,600 km southwest of New Delhi, Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the toll was likely to go up as
the bus was jam-packed at the time of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The mishap occurred when the private bus hit an electric post
at Pizhaku area. The mangled bus was being cut open and a clear
picture would be known only later. The bodies were charred beyond
recognition and the injured have been admitted to a medical
college hospital nearby, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
