<HEADLINE> Industrialized Nations Are Main Culprits of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- An Indian noted geophysicist,
Dr. J. G. Negi said Thursday that the industrialized nations are
the main culprits behind atmosphere pollution and depletion of
ozone layer causing global warming phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The panic being created over global warming and greenhouse
effect is guided by vested economic interests of industrialized
nations. India need not fear the global warming phenomenon since
its contribution of greenhouse gas emissions is negligible
compared with developed countries, Press Trust of India (PTI)
quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
The emission of carbon dioxide, methane, chlorofluorocarbons
and other greenhouse gases from Western countries touched around
2,500 million tones per year while the contribution of entire
developing nations was around 1,000 million tones, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
