<HEADLINE> Santos Win First Major Title in 14 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Santos won its first
title in 14 years after taking the South American Conmebol Cup on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Santos, Pele's former club, won the final 1-0 on aggregate
after Wednesday's goalless draw. It was their first major trophy
in 14 years since the Paulista championship in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian club played the second half with 10 players as
Eduardo marques was sent off early in the second half. But their
goal-keeper Zetti made a string of fine saves to deny the Argent
ines.
</P>
<P>
It was the fifth time a Brazilian side has won the title since
it began in 1992. Argentine clubs have won in the other two
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
