<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Fpokesman on Jiang's Coming Japan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
Japan visit next month will further consolidate and promote the
good-neighbor relations between the two countries and propel
the healthy and stable Sino-Japanese relations into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang made the remarks
at today's regular press conference.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan are engaged in consultations on the date and
other arrangements for Jiang's visit, according to him.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether the two sides will discuss historical
problems during the visit, Tang said Japanese militarism committed
serious crimes against China and other Asian countries during
World War II, and this is undeniable.
</P>
<P>
He added China holds that the past experiences will be a guide
for the future if not forgotten.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Japan will develop friendly
Sino-Japanese cooperation on the basis of respecting historical
facts and promoting peace and progress.
</P>
<P>
Adopting a correct attitude towards historical problems on the
part of the Japanese government will help safeguard the political
basis for Sino-Japanese relations and enhance mutual understanding
and trust between Japan and its Asian neighbors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
