<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday as retailers taking
profit softened institutional support on key blue chips.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dropped
2.81 points to 421.56, the all-share Emas Index shed 0.96 of a
point to 110.29, the Industrial Index lost 7.13 points to 814.13
while the Second Board Index managed to climb 1.11 points to
103.95.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers 410 to 235 while 123 counters were
unchanged, 148 untraded and 36 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was lower at 172.392 million shares totaling
271.855 million ringgit (71.54 million U.S. dollars) from 290.163
million shares valued at 445.821 million ringgit (117.321 million
U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover was lower at 146.139 million shares
worth 234.965 million ringgit (61.832 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 273.242 million shares valued at 420.072 million
ringgit (110.545 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover increased to 26.253 million shares
valued at 36.890 million ringgit (9.707 million U.S. dollars) from
16.921 million shares worth 25.748 million ringgit (6.775 million
U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover rose to 10.171 million shares valued at
17.927 million ringgit (4.717 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 4.244 million shares totaling 8.791 million ringgit
(2.313 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 5.573
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
10.146 million shares, construction 15.162 million shares,
trading/services 34.791 million shares, infrastructure 485,000
shares, finance 24.813 million shares, hotels 772,000 shares,
properties 31.080 million shares, plantation 5.146 million shares,
mining 430,400 shares, trusts 83,000 shares, closed/fund 52,000
shares and loans 17.605 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
