<HEADLINE> China Plans Liu Shaoqi Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China will open a large-scale
exhibition on Friday to commemorate the 100th birth anniversary of
late President Liu Shaoqi.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will feature 210 photographs and approximately
300 pieces of cultural relics, art works and documents, as well as
replicas of Liu's home. Some 200-odd items or originals, according
to the Museum of the Chinese Revolution.
</P>
<P>
The Central Archives provided 13 original documents which
record Liu's revolutionary experiences.
</P>
<P>
Visitors will also be able to view a rare copy of Liu's famous
thesis on Communist virtues and various other documents belonging
to Wang Guangmei, Liu's widow.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Culture, State Bureau of Cultural Relics
and five additional departments.
</P>
<P>
Liu was born on November 24, 1898 and passed away in 1969.
</P>
</TEXT>
