<HEADLINE> Air Macao to Open New Route to Sanya City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao will inaugurate its
regular weekly service between Macao and the southern city of
Sanya in Hainan Province on October 25, sources with the airline
company said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Flight NX9178 will depart Macao every Sunday at 12:35 and
arrive in Sanya at 14:10. The return flight of NX9177 will leave
Sanya the same day at 15:00 and arrive in Macao at 16:25.
</P>
<P>
Sanya is a flourishing seaport city of China's southern tip of
Hainan Province, and a natural tourist resort ideal place for
swimming, surfing and sunbathing.
</P>
<P>
Sanya will be Air Macao's 10th destination in the mainland
areas of China following Beijing, Shanghai, Xiamen, Wuhan, Fuzhou,
 Nanjing, Chongqing, Zhengzhou and Ningbo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
