<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Biggest Carpet Woven in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- World's biggest hand-woven
carpet has been produced in the city of Ben in Iran's western
province of Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari, the official news agency IRNA
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Director General of the provincial welfare department Siyavash
Ahmadi said Thursday that the carpet of 1,000 square meters was
produced over a span of three years by 84 weavers.
</P>
<P>
Ahmadi said the carpet, with a cost of about 500 million rials
(about 166,000 U.S. dollars) was valued at 1.2 billion rials
(about 400,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Iran is well-known for its traditional hand-woven carpet,
which ranks first in the country's non-oil exports.
</P>
<P>
But in recent years, the Iranian carpet industry has been
challenged in the world market by products of China and India.
</P>
</TEXT>
