<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP to Assist China in Two Cooperative Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) and China signed two cooperative projects this
afternoon in Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
One project centers on promoting the development of handicrafts
development in Tibet's Qomolangma Nature Preserve (QNP), and the
other extends the ongoing China Rural Officials Training Program.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish government will provide over 1.38 million US
dollars for implementation of the two projects. UNDP Resident
Beijing Representative Kerstin Leitner and Liang Dan, director
general of the China International Center for Economic and
Technical Exchanges, signed the agreements.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the three-year Tibet project to increase the
handicraft production of poor Tibetan households in order to
alleviate poverty and diversify sources of income in Tingri and
Nyalam counties.
</P>
<P>
The project will improve management and marketing, handicraft
production and provide small loans to poor households lacking
access to capital needed to start small businesses.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the four-year training project which will carried
out through the year 2000 is to improve the implementation of grass
roots self-government by providing village committee members with
training in the realm of public and financial management.
</P>
<P>
The project has supported the China Rural Officials Training
Center under the Ministry of Civil Affairs since 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
