<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
Singapore Stock Market Thursday in what dealers were calling the
initial stages of a technical correction to the market's recent
gains.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) retreated 23.41 points
in active dealings to end at 1,117.50 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said a surge in share prices at the open was wiped out
by profit-taking which began creeping into the market shortly
before midday.
</P>
<P>
They noted selling speeded up as European players entered the
market in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover decreased to 458.95 million units valued at
581.06 million Singapore dollars (358.08 million U.S. dollars).
Losers edged out gainers by 266 to 49 with 108 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 16,25 million parcel of KepLand which
topped the active chart. Goldtrn was the second most heavily
traded stock on the exchange with a turnover of 23.74 million
units. Ipco was next with 20.89 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the ascent of the day as it rose by 40 cents to
18.10 Singapore dollars at close. OUE went up 14 cents to finish
at 2.80 Singapore dollars. Ipco was up 13 cents to end at 0.53
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA F was the biggest loser of the day with a
loss of 90 cents to close at 9.40 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem
retreated 55 cents to close at 8.00 Singapore dollars. SPH was 50
cents lower to end at 13.90 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
