<HEADLINE> New IT Service Launched in HK to Enhance Productivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Productivity
Council (HKPC) and Hongkong Telecom (HkT) signed a memorandum of
understanding (MOU) here Thursday to jointly introduce the world's
first broadband business application service to Hong Kong business
community.
</P>
<P>
The Productivity-on-Demand service will provide all-in-one
business solutions including high speed Internet access,
integrated communications, business information, online service
bureau and training services to local companies.
</P>
<P>
Under the memorandum, HkT, the biggest telecom company in Hong
Kong, will provide the broadband infrastructure required for the
development and delivery of Productivity-on-Demand, while HKPC
will provide up-to-date business information, knowledge bases, and
online bureau services to users.
</P>
<P>
K.H. Cheng, director of product and e-commerce of HkT, said the
service is launched to enhance the competitiveness of local
business, in particular small and medium sized enterprises (SMEs)
through utilization of advanced information technology (IT) and
broadband network.
</P>
<P>
Through this service, local companies will be able to save
costs, enhance productivity and improve their competitive edge.
</P>
<P>
HKPC Executive Director Thomas Tang said that
Productivity-on-Demand will be available to Hong Kong companies by
the first quarter of next year.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said that the service is a joint initiative between HkT
and HKPC to create and promote a simple and user-friendly means to
adopt IT within the Hong Kong business community.
</P>
<P>
As a high speed broadband application of integrated business
tailor-made for Hong Kong's SMEs, Productivity-on-Demand enables
them to fully enjoy the convenience of e-commerce and speed up
their pace entering the world market, Cheng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
