<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Colonel Samuel Marques Mota,
visiting chief of the Macao Fire Brigade, expressed the belief
here Thursday that existing close cooperation between Macao
and Hong Kong in fire services will be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the passing out parade of 10 Probationary Station
Officers and 136 Firemen at the Hong Kong Fire Services training
School, Mota said that the fire brigades of Macao and Hong Kong
have always maintained a strong bond with each other.
