<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region Opens New Air Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region opened a new air route today flying from Beijing
via the region's capital city of Yinchuan to Hangzhou, capital of
east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The region has so far opened 12 air routes. The new air service
has been contracted by a local industrial company, is operated by
United Airlines of China, and is available every Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new route is expected to promote the opening up of the
region and to give impetus to cooperation between the country's
western and eastern areas. 
