<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Slightly Lower Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian rupiah was closed at
7,500/7,750 to the U.S. dollar on the Jakarta inter-bank spot
market Thursday, declining by 400 points compared with Wednesday's
close of 7,100/7,300 per U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said a statement by Coordinating Minister for Economy,
Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita helped contain the
rupiah's rally.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters Wednesday, Ginandjar said: "I personally
expect the rupiah will not strengthen to below the 5,000 rupiah
level because it will hurt our exports. I think 7,000 to 8,000
rupiah is the best equilibrium level for now."
</P>
<P>
Money market analyst Farial Anwar agreed with the government
that the currency should not jump drastically.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has been advancing significantly during the past
couple of weeks, touching the 7,000 level at one point during the
Wednesday trading session. The currency, which plunged to its
lowest level of 17,000 against the greenback in January, was
hovering at a range between 10,000 and 11,000 rupiah last month.
</P>
<P>
"The rupiah must consolidate at around 7,000 for the time being
and start declining by about 200 or 300 points in the weeks to
come so the people have gotten used to the level," Farial said,
adding that a drastic rise will also invite speculation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
