<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Confers with Russian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister
General Chi Haotian and his Russian counterpart Marshall Igor
Dmitriyevich Sergeyev agreed here today that certain countries'
plans to develop theatre missile defense system will arouse new
arms race and threaten world and regional peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Chi and visiting Sergeyev also exchanged views on international
and regional security issues of common concern during the talks
here today.
</P>
<P>
Chi extended a welcome to Sergeyev, who is in China for the
first time, and indicated that the visit, a major event in
Sino-Russian military relations, not only helps maintain and
develop the existing friendship and cooperative relations between
the two armed forces, but also promotes the comprehensive
development of Sino-Russian strategic cooperative partnership
oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission
(CMC) and state councillor, noted that the two countries are
cooperating closely on the basis of good-neighborly friendship and
mutual trust toward the goal of establishing a new international
political and economical order featuring fairness and
reasonableness. It is vital to maintaining global peace and
development, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that China highly values the agreements reached among
five mid-Asian countries including China and Russia which says
that mutual trust will be enhanced and armed forces reduced. He
pointed out that the two documents is of tremendous importance to
strengthening good-neighborly friendship among those countries,
and to maintaining peace, stability and prosperity in the region
and in the world.
</P>
<P>
That China, Russia and some other mid-Asian countries chose the
path of trust, disarmament, peace and cooperation contributes
enormously to world peace, and sets a good example for the
international community.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev said he highly values the state-to-state and
army-to-army relations between the two countries, adding that both
countries share identical or similar views on a series of
international and regional security issues, and have carried on
fruitful cooperation in international affairs. He expressed the
hope to further promote the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
CMC member and Director of the General Equipment Department of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army General Cao Gangchuan also
was present at the talks. 
</P>
