<HEADLINE> EU Opens Regional ECHO Office in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Community
Humanitarian Office (ECHO) has opened a regional office in Dhaka,
Bangladesh, to serve as the center for the new Disaster
Preparedness program for Southeast Asia and Bangladesh, the
European Commission announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ECHO office, the European Union's humanitarian body, will
use the Dhaka office to assess the general humanitarian situation
and the needs of the population in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Dhaka office will advise ECHO headquarters in Brussels on
its assistance programs and ensure the follow-up of those
programs. It will also monitor and coordinate the implementation
of humanitarian aid in the Indian sub-continent.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, ECHO has appropriated 6.25 million ECU (5.78
million US dollars) for humanitarian aid in Bangladesh. The
financing has mainly covered emergency operations providing relief
to victims of tornados and floods. 
