<HEADLINE> Pakistan Expresses Satisfaction over Waiver Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Thursday expressed
satisfaction that the U.S. President has been given a waiver
authority to lift economic sanctions which were imposed after
Pakistan conducted its nuclear tests in May.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Foreign Office said Thursday in a press
statement that the lifting of the sanctions will remove the
coercive atmosphere and pave the way for a cooperative approach on
their respective concerns.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the grant of waiver, when exercised in
favor of Pakistan, will remove an important road block which will
enable the two countries to overcome the difficulties towards
opening a new chapter in bilateral relations. 
</P>
