<HEADLINE> Italian Skaters Take Lead at World Junior Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Italians got an ovation all
the way through the the pleasing tune as they cruised to their
openning success in compulsory dance of the ice dancing at the
world junior figure skating series here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The whole event was culminated when Flavia Ottaviani and
Massimo Scali were awarded the highest scores in presentation.
</P>
<P>
The five judges scored the Italians 4.8, 4.7, 4.8, 5.1, 4.8 in
presentation and 4.6, 4.7, 4.8, 4.3, 4.7 in skill as the skaters
from the United States and France took the next positions.
</P>
<P>
Italians' coach Rizzo Walter played down the initial
performance for it is just the beginning.
</P>
<P>
"You know it is only the first step, so I do not want to say
much. I could tell you at the end of the competition. They are
stronger in free dancing."
</P>
<P>
The host who fielded three pairs failed to meet the
expectation of the local fans but still was hailed as "very good"
by their coach.
</P>
<P>
"Their performances are very good, they are so young that they
are very promising," said Xi Hongyan. "But Chinese skaters still
have a long way to go in ice dancing, the presentation and basic
skills leave much to be desired."
</P>
<P>
While Walter gave a high opinion of the Chinese skaters.
"They have improved a lot, they will be very dangerous in the
future, they have improved a lot." said Walter.
</P>
<P>
The series spans three days at the first leg which drew 68
entries from fifteen countries and regions. 
</P>
