<HEADLINE> HK-Listed China Telecom Buoyant Despite Asian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom, the largest
overseas-listed mainland stock, has taken the lead at the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange despite the current financial turmoil that has
afflicted many parts of Asia and other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
Since it was issued last October, the red-chip leader has seen
the market price of its shares increased by 26.3 percent from the
issuing price of 11.8 HK dollars per share.
</P>
<P>
A China Telecom spokesman told Xinhua here Thursday that the
company's total market value has reached 20 billion U.S. dollars,
fourth among listed firms in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman attributed the company's growth to arduous
efforts to improve its marketing ability and internal management.
</P>
<P>
Following the acquisition of Jiangsu Mobile this June, China
Telecom now owns cellular telecommunications businesses in the
provinces of Guangdong, Zhejiang and Jiangsu. The number of its
cellular phone subscribers had topped 5.45 million by the end of
June.
</P>
<P>
According to the company's interim reports, its core business
profit rate and net profit rate reached 30 percent and 29 percent,
respectively. 
</P>
