<HEADLINE> Disputes Erupt at Indian Education Ministers Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Severe disputes erupted soon
after the education ministers conference began here Thursday with
some state ministers accusing the ruling Bharatiya Janata Party
(BJP) of trying to introduce Hindu ideology in education.
</P>
<P>
Education ministers of several states including BJP's allies
staged a walkout to protest attempts to impose Hindutva (Hindu
ideas) in the non-official agenda for the conference.
</P>
<P>
Singing of "saraswati vandan", a prayer to the Hindu goddess of
learning, had become a focal point of protest that had been
building over circulation of non-official agenda for the
conference by the Human Resource Development Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Faced with strong opposition at the meeting, Human Resource
Development Minister M. Manohar Joshi was forced to drop the
controversial non-official part of the agenda.
</P>
<P>
BJP leaders have had different voices over the controversial
issue so far. While Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee in his
inaugural speech said that there must be no place for religious
bigotry and intolerance, BJP spokesman Venkaiah Naidu said the
same day that the BJP supported suggestion for "Indianizing and
spiritualizing" education. 
