<HEADLINE> Russia Warns against Disruptions in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Foreign Ministry,
on behalf of the Contact Group, warned Thursday all forces in
Kosovo against disrupting the peace agreements, according to
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with visiting Greek Foreign
Minister Theodoros Pangalos, Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov
said, "We are really very worried" over the resumption of military
action in the troubled region.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov said there are people who would like to disrupt the
efforts of the world community to achieve a peace settlement.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to remind you of the fact that Resolution
No.119, passed by the UN Security Council, applies in full to both
Belgrade and the Albanians," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov urged all the parties in Kosovo to take advantage of
political channels for settling the situation.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos denounced a double standard in handling the Kosovo
crisis, saying those who used a one-sided approach to solving the
problem are responsible for the current situation.
</P>
<P>
He said Greece has always stated that within the framework of
NATO and the European Union, a settlement can be achieved in
Kosovo. But the initiatives should be balanced and not directed at
only one of the parties concerned, he said. 
</P>
