<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition hall displaying
gifts and souvenirs received by the People's Liberation Army of
China during foreign contacts opened to public at the Military
Museum in Beijing earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese People's Liberation Army Foreign Exchange and
Friendship Hall" covers 900 square meters of floor space in the
Military Museum. The exhibits include more than 500 gifts and
souvenirs selected from those received by the PLA over the past
decades.
</P>
<P>
The pieces on display are considered historical evidence of the
PLA's foreign exchanges and also reflect the military cultures of
the donor countries.  
