<HEADLINE> Chinese Trade Unions Elect New Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Delegates to the 13th National
Congress of Chinese Trade Unions today elected its new leadership,
the 13th executive committee of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions (ACFTU).
</P>
<P>
At the third plenary session of the congress held in Beijing
this afternoon, more than 1,600 delegates elected 258 members
of the ACFTU executive committee through a multi-candidate
election.
</P>
<P>
The 41 members of the 13th Funding Supervision Committee of the
ACFTU was also elected during the session.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1925, the ACFTU is the leading organ of trade unions
in all places and industrial sectors in China. The national
congress, held once every five years, is the paramount body of
Chinese trade unions.
</P>
<P>
The newly elected executive committee will hold its first
plenary meeting tomorrow to elect the presidium members and the
president and vice presidents of the ACFTU. 
</P>
