<HEADLINE> HK's Foreign Currency Reserves at 88.4 Bln Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's foreign currency
assets amounted to 88.4 billion U.S. dollars at the end of
September, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) announced here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This shows that in terms of foreign currency reserves ranking,
Hong Kong remains the third largest in the world, after Japan and
the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
However, the newly released figure represented 3.7 billion U.S.
dollars less than that of the previous month.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the HKMA attributed the drop mainly to the
settlement of the 4.4 billion U.S. dollars unsettled forward
exchange contracts announced last month with the August foreign
currency asset figures. 
</P>
