<HEADLINE> Big Swindler Arrested in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong Provincial
Public Security Department announced Thursday that Luo Dazhan has
been arrested for swindling 9.7 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The case has been moved to the Taishan city procurator by the
police, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
In November 1995, Luo, claiming to be the president of a
so-called China Town Group in Cambodia, opened a company in
Taishan and began his schemes.
</P>
<P>
In the same year, Luo signed contracts with some local
companies in Taishan on four large infrastructure projects. Since
then, he has done nothing on the projects while continuing to sign
more contracts with over 140 other companies, posing as an
exporting agent for stone materials.
</P>
<P>
He then told the city government of Taishan that he finally had
enough funds for the four infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Local police arrested Luo this April and seized nearly 8
million yuan of the fraudulently gained funds. 
</P>
