<HEADLINE> Fireworks Festival Ends in Liuyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Fireworks formed a colorful
waterfall of 1,000 meters in total length in the sky. That is an
outstanding work shown at today's closing ceremony of the '98 China
Liuyang International Fireworks Festival.
</P>
<P>
The waterfall fireworks amazed the overseas audiences from more
than 10 countries at the festival, which ended in Liuyang City,
central China's Hunan Province, today.
</P>
<P>
Liuyang, which started manufacturing fireworks about 1,300
years ago, is hometown of fireworks.
</P>
<P>
The city's fireworks sell well in more than 60 countries and
regions. And nearly 60 percent of China's fireworks for export
come from Liuyang City with more than 700 fireworks factories.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that Liuyang fireworks will be set off to
mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of New China, the return
of Macao to the motherland, and the New Year's day in 1999.
</P>
<P>
A seminar on fireworks standards for the United States also
closed today. 
