<HEADLINE> Chang'an Boulevard to be Wider and Brighter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Chang'an Boulevard, Beijing's
main thoroughfare running east and west straight through downtown,
will take on a new look before China's 50th National Day in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, secretary of the Communist Party of China Beijing
Committee, said today that the entire boulevard and its extensions
will become much wider, cleaner and brighter before the 50th
National Day.
</P>
<P>
The greenery on both sides of the road will be expanded by 10.8
hectares, and the width of the sidewalks on either side will also
be extended to five to eight meters, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the lighting of Tiananmen Square at night also will be
changed. All chimneys within 200 meters along both sides of the
street will be removed, and measures will also be taken to rectify
car parking along Chang'an.  
