<HEADLINE> China Crushes Qatar in Asian Under-19 Soccer Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Yan scored a
splendid goal in Thursday's match against Qatar, lifting China to
the same footing with the other three teams in Group B of the
31rst Asian Youth Under-19 soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
China, together with Qatar, South Korea and Japan, gained four
points, while Iraq had zero.
</P>
<P>
Qatar made thrushing advances at the beginning of the match
held at Chiang Mai's 700-Year Main Stadium, but met with strong
resistance. Abdula M Alrasheedi got a yellow card less than five
minutes into the first half.
</P>
<P>
Qatar missed a great scoring chance when Sellman M Almeamari
got cross two meters from the almost open gate but fell down.
</P>
<P>
China lost one player only 25 minutes into the first half when
Liu Yujian got a red card for fouling against Mohmd Gulam.
</P>
<P>
However, China, kept its composure and managed to press
forward with several execellent but unsuccessful shots. Qatari
goal keeper Ali Hilal Najm fell into the net when trying to catch
a shot that was fired over the post. It took almost one minute
before he could stand up.
</P>
<P>
Although with one man less, China dominated the second half.
Li Yan scored a marvellous goal when the Chinese made a
counter-attack 20 minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
The second half saw Qatar having two yellow cards.
Goal-keeper Ali Hilal Najm had two great saves. Then Qatar had a
great chance to score two minutes before the match ended when
Chinese goalie Liu Yunfei palmed off the shot from a close range.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Chen Jingang said his players played well and
kept calm during the game. He said Qatar was stronger in terms
of skills but China laid emphasis on team-work and what he called
"team spirit".
</P>
<P>
Qatari coach Abdulla Juma said Qatar, with one-man advantage,
should have won the match. But the team lacked cooperation and
harmony.
</P>
<P>
He cited fatigue as another reason for the failure, saying his
players had played three games without enough time to relax.
</P>
<P>
Qatar played more games than the other teams in Group B, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In another match Thursday, Japan beat Iraq 6-2. Saturday's
matches are Qatar vs Japan and Iraq vs South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
